<br>
I've played countless hours, and taken many long breaks from EQ but have come back (just did recently again) every time because it's still the best MMORPG to date, and I still find it enjoyable, but only when I take some time off in between stints of playing.<br>
<br>
People talk about how it's so addictive, and I guess initially I felt that too, but the ONLY reason I log in these days is because it's still fun (most of the time).<br>
<br>
It's extremely simple....are you having fun?  Yes?  Then play.  No?  Then don't......... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugenji27.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Genji27</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/18/01 8:09:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How the hell do you quit?</span><hr size=1> Realize that EQ is hindering your RL. Give/sell away all your stuff. Cancel account. Toss CDs out the window. Find a new less time consuming hobby/game (I only spend like 1/3 or 1/4 of the time on DAoC as I did with EQ) to keep yourself entertained if you get bored.<br>
<br>
I still get the urge to come back occasionally just to chat and spend time with friends and guildies, but I just use e-mail/icq/aim/phone to talk to them now. It really helps if you can keep in touch and talk with your friends and guildies often, it really gets rid of the urge to actually log in. Of course, some people just don't like checking their e-mails or replying. /flip those people <p>Genji
<BR>
